HEADWORD: namedrop
<hw>namedrop</hw> <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To refer to people that one
assumes one's interlocutors admire so as to impress them; same as to
<er>drop names</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> drop names.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>namedropper</ent>⟦br⟧
